      "writtenOn": "2021-06-18T15:05:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The name `asBlendMode` really threw me for a loop (I actually wrote and deleted a long comment here based on a misconception of what was going on here).\n\nI think the root of the misconception was that \"asFoo\" and \"isFoo\" makes it seem like a Paint *is* a blend mode, instead of a Paint *has* a blend mode. Seems like a nitpick, but it took me several minutes to actually understand what these APIs were meant to do, and I think that\u0027s the root cause of my initial confusion.\n\nWe might be better off putting these sorts of helpers on the SkBlender, then just let the user call `paint.getBlender()-\u003eisBlendMode(kDstOut)` or something. Alternatively, we ought to try and think of more descriptive names for this API.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 497,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 497,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "85addb407f8999f371cc761118106919687f62af",
